Ad Text:
Data and Integrations Manager

Type: Full-time
Location: Sydney, Melbourne or Brisbane
Reports to: Head of Application Engineering

As the Data and Integrations Manager at I-MED Radiology, you'll play a pivotal role in shaping and delivering the technology that underpins critical healthcare services across Australia and New Zealand. You'll lead the design and implementation of HL7-based integrations, ensuring secure, reliable, and high-quality solutions for both our business and our clients.

This role will see you establish and mature I-MED's data capability, working closely with business leaders, IT leadership, and enterprise architects to define the future state of data engineering, and to build the teams, systems, and structures required to achieve it.

As an inspiring people leader, you are an exceptional communicator and influencer who drives operational excellence through empowerment, accountability, and collaboration. You're equally comfortable in strategic conversations or diving into the technical detail when it matters.

Who we are

I-MED Radiology Network is Australia and New Zealand's largest diagnostic imaging network, offering medical imaging and radiology services including x-ray, PET, CT, MRI, Nuclear Medicine, Ultrasound, Mammography and interventional procedures.

At I-MED Radiology Network there is a strong belief that we can be the most respected and trusted medical imaging specialists in the world. That's our vision, underpinned by our purpose - to help save lives and reduce uncertainty. We strive to be the provider of choice, providing answers to health questions and delivering high quality care and service to our patients and referrers, every time.

Benefits

We offer a wide range of exclusive benefits - including health insurance discounts, salary packaging, Fitness Passport access, lifestyle perks through Perkbox, I-MED services for your family, and comprehensive wellbeing support.

What you'll do


Lead the design, development, and maintenance of hospital integration solutions
Oversee the delivery of integration and data solutions aligned with architectural strategies and standards
Define and implement patterns, schemas, and storage solutions that support scalable data and integration frameworks
Partner with business and IT stakeholders to evolve and continuously improve data and integration architecture
Manage vendor relationships to ensure optimal service delivery and performance
Oversee release management, testing, and system maintenance activities
Collaborate with Clinic Leaders and business stakeholders to support and drive adoption of IT solutions
Troubleshoot and resolve issues in line with company ITSM standards for service requests, incidents, problems, and change management
Work closely with infrastructure and operations teams to automate monitoring, response, and recovery processes
Participate in an on-call roster providing 24/7 support for critical incidents

What you've done


Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, or a related discipline
Experience in healthcare IT, focusing on integrations and/or data management
Proven expertise in HL7 and DICOM standards and protocols
Strong understanding of data management principles, including data modelling, ETL, and data quality
Experience working with RIS and PACS applications
Demonstrated leadership and team management skills
Excellent communication and stakeholder engagement abilities

Shape the future of healthcare data and integration at Australia's leading radiology network.

Position Brief - Transport Systems Analyst

About the team

The Transport Systems Intelligence (TSI) team is a fun, dynamic team within the Transport Operations Business Unit. Our vision is to foster a safer transport environment by optimising operational efficiency, empowering informed decisions for network operators and establishing the groundwork for transport technology advancements.

About the role

The Transport Network Analyst will provide support to the Principal Transport Network Analyst in undertaking transport and traffic analysis for the Gold Coast transport system, with a focus on optimising the safety and efficiency of the road network.

This includes:

· Develop route and corridor traffic planning studies to maximise the operational efficiency of the Gold Coast road network.

· Assist in monitoring and reporting on the performance of strategic corridors and roads of significance.

· Provide technical advice to support traffic engineering and planning initiatives.

· Preparation of traffic assessments.

· Assist in identifying network pinch points and network optimisation treatments.

· Coordinate and liaise with internal stakeholders and external consultants to deliver efficient outcomes.

We’re looking for people who have:

Bachelor’s degree relevant to the position (e.g. engineering, planning) or equivalent industry experience.

· Demonstrated experience as a traffic professional.

· Experience with using SIDRA, and other microsimulation software.

· Knowledge of modern traffic modelling methodologies and practices.

· Unrestricted ‘C’ Class Drivers Licence.

· You thrive on applying innovative approaches to programs and problem solving.

· You foster positive relationships with stakeholders.

· You contribute to supporting outcomes that help build a connected and intelligent transport network for the Gold Coast.

· You have excellent verbal, written and interpersonal communication skills; with experience in developing grant submissions, education awareness campaigns and writing reports.

· You work productively in a team environment and foster positive relationships with other team members.

About the role
The Data Scientist, part of the Data Science Chapter within Product & Commercial, plays a crucial role in driving AGL's profitability. They build and maintain advanced data models, analyse complex datasets, and develop predictive models to solve business problems and uncover growth opportunities.

Reporting functionally to the GM of Product & Commercial and the Data Science chapter lead, Data Scientists are embedded in cross-functional teams to support business objectives. They maintain strong ties with the Data Science Chapter for capability development, knowledge sharing, and aligning on data practices, while being accountable for upholding data standards and achieving business goals.

What you'll be doing:

Build and iterate machine learning models to tackle business challenges like customer segmentation and marketing optimization.
Enhance model performance through feature engineering, hyperparameter tuning, and ensemble methods.
Conduct experiments to test hypotheses and derive actionable insights from data.
Create compelling visualizations to effectively communicate complex insights to stakeholders.
Identify new applications for data science to generate refined insights.
Stay updated on industry trends and emerging technologies to drive innovation

About you:

Previous demonstrated experience in customer segmentation and predictive behaviour modelling.
Strong analytical skills, with experience in applying statistical techniques to solve business problems.
Proficient in developing and implementing predictive models, segmentation models, and other statistical models using tools such as R, Python, or SAS (Python preferred).
Basic SQL skills and understanding of version control systems (ie. Git repository)
Experience in using data visualization tools such as Tableau or Power BI to effectively communicate complex findings to both technical and non-technical stakeholders.
Knowledge of the energy industry, including familiarity with energy consumption patterns, regulatory frameworks, and industry-specific challenges. - preferred - not essential.

Ad Text:
Great opportunity for an Automation Engineer with up to 2 years experience.
Due to internal promotion, an excellent position has become available working with a renowned Global Pharmaceutical Manufacturer based in the South Eastern suburbs near Clayton.
Apply now for this rare opportunity! Here are the details below:

Reporting to the Automation Manager, the Automation Engineer position is a subject matter expert for automation, electrical and control systems.

The focus of this role is to ensure reliability, robustness, throughput and security of new and existing equipment/systems. This is done by completing or contributing towards projects and implementing other minor modifications/changes as required. This role contributes to the overall plan towards Industry 4.0 and the integration of other business systems such as SAP with factory automation.

Additionally, this position supports the factory with day to day issues that arise involving the automation and electrical systems including PLC/SCADA and other OT software.

Day to day responsibilities include:

Project support/system design

·       Implement minor projects and participate as a team member for larger projects.

·       Implement PLC hardware and software changes. Make changes to HMIs/SCADAs and other OT systems as required

·       Undertake electrical designs including cabinet layouts

·       Produce electrical drawings for modifications

·       Prepare design specifications and work packages Technicians and Contractors

·       Develop User Requirement Specifications (URS) and Qualification documents (IQ/OQ/PQ)

·       Complete commissioning and validation/qualification where required

·       Design, program and document small automation projects autonomously

·       Coordinate contractors and tradespeople to perform automation works including both software and hardware

Day to day support

Provide technical support to resolve day to day issues on the PLC network, servers and automation software

·       Support Technicians with troubleshooting issues related to automation

·       Investigate deviation incidents and implement corrective actions

·       Become subject matter expert for automation system software (Iltis, 3WS, C# applications)

·       Administer and manage applications on the factory network such as 3WS and user management on Active Directory

·       Update and upgrade automation and Windows operating systems to ensure that cyber security risks are minimised

·       Provide support to production on new equipment

Documentation

Ensure that adequate and accurate documentation is generated and stored with a high attention to detail

·       Manage and complete electrical drawing updates

·       Perform critical spares assessments

·       Ensure software backups are correctly stored in the backups repository

·       Ensure that appropriate system documentation is filed in the Engineering DMS folders

·       Ensure that safety design, validation and testing documentation is filed in the Engineering DMS folders

·       Create Isolation Procedures where required

·       Complete Change Management documentation

GxP

Ensure the principles of GxP are observed through all activities

·       Maintain an understanding of the principles of GxP

·       Ensure routine tasks are covered by approved Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs)

·       Ensure relevant changes are covered by Change Control Procedures (CCPs) with appropriate authorisation and testing

Work related requirements/selection criteria:

Education and qualifications required:

Bachelor Engineering (Electrical, Mechatronics or Software)

Experience required:

Experience in a manufacturing environment or as a system integrator (pharmaceutical, cosmetics, food or chemical industries would be relevant) is desirable

Skills required:

·       Strong fault finding and problem solving abilities

·       Ability to work effectively in a team or individually

·       High attention to detail

·       Good communication skills, both written and oral

·       Experience programming, maintaining and commissioning PLC hardware and software (Siemens, Allen-Bradley etc.)

·       Experience configuring, maintaining and commissioning SCADA/Historian/OPC software packages

·       Programming experience (.NET C#, ladder (Rockwell, Siemens))

·       Understanding of industrial Ethernet networks (VLANs, subnets)

·       Experience designing safety systems in accordance with AS/NZS 4024

·       Electrical drawing design and updating (AutoCAD or similar)

·       GAMP5 experience (desirable)

Must have PR, AU or NZ Citizenship to be eligible to apply.

Ad Text:
Job Title: Mid-Level AI Analyst - Governance & Ethics
Location: Sydney CBD
Employment Type: Full-time / long term contract opportunity
Salary: Negotiable contract rate on offer

About the Role

We are seeking a hands-on Mid-Level AI Analyst, and this role is ideal for someone passionate about AI governance, ethics, and responsible AI frameworks, who enjoys translating complex technical risks into practical advice and solutions.
You will work across government, enterprise, and technical teams to assess AI initiatives, monitor compliance, and support the implementation of robust governance processes. This is not a policy-making role , it's analytical, advisory, and deeply hands-on, offering exposure to cutting-edge AI projects in a high-impact environment.

Key Responsibilities

Conduct AI governance and ethics assessments across projects, identifying potential risks, bias, fairness, and compliance issues.
Support implementation of AI governance frameworks, approval gates, and monitoring processes.
Collaborate with policy, IT, legal, privacy, and business teams to provide clear, actionable guidance on AI projects.
Document and report findings, including risk assessments, dashboards, and governance committee materials.
Stay up to date with AI regulatory requirements, privacy laws, and ethical AI principles, ensuring projects align with best practice.
Assist in embedding responsible AI practices and frameworks.


Skills & Experience
Essential:

Hands-on experience in AI governance, ethics, and responsible AI frameworks.
Understanding of ethical AI principles: bias/fairness, & transparency.
Experience assessing AI projects for compliance, risk, and governance concerns.
Strong analytical skills and ability to review data sets, model outputs, or AI tools.
Experience with ServiceNow or similar governance/tracking tools.
Excellent communication skills to translate technical risks into clear advice for senior management.


Desirable / Nice-to-Have:

Background in government/public sector, consulting, finance, regulated industries, academia, or tech companies with AI governance exposure.
Knowledge of AI regulatory requirements, PIAs, or model risk frameworks.
Experience supporting governance committees, dashboards, and reporting frameworks.

"If AI governance and ethics excite you, we want to hear from you!"
